            "description": "Gave a lecture at the 3rd Annual Transit Oriented Development Asia congress to developers, railway officials and government officials about Maak Plaats! (Make Space!), the TOD strategy used in the province of North-Holland. This strategy focuses on three different levels of scale; the railway network, railway corridor and the individual stations. For the latter the so-called butterfly model is used to assess the development opportunities of a station area.\n",
