                    "company": "Provincie Noord-Holland",
                    "description": "Member of the program team station areas.\nAdvising on policies and role the province should take regarding the development of station areas. In this role I try to put the lessons identified in my PhD-research into practice. A specific outcome of this is that the province has embraced the corridor as a logical unit for coordinating land use and transport developments at the regional level and has recognized that for such coordination to succeed a more guiding role of the province is needed. The first railway section for which a corridor strategy will be drafted and implemented is the Zaancorridor.\nCurrently I am involved in preparing an implementation agreement for the Zaancorridor (the railway section between Amsterdam central station and Heerhugowaard station). This agreement should make clear how developments are going to be prioritised and how functional programmes are going to be distributed along the railway corridor. For this the province works closely with the railway sector, the city-region and the local municipalities involved.",
